<h2><b><span style="color:red;">Test 2.3</span></b></h2>
Which of the following is a significant property of LTI systems? 
  
    <ul class="answers">
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q3ai"/><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a" id="q3a"><label for="q3a">If the input is $x(t)$ and the impulse response is $h(t)$, then the output $y(t)$ is $y(t)=h(t)*x(t)$.                       </label><br>       
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q3bi"/><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b" id="q3b"><label for="q3b">The response to an eternal sinusoid is an eternal sinusoid at the same frequency.                                            </label><br>          
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q3ci"/><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c" id="q3c"><label for="q3c">The response to a linear combination of inputs is the same linear combination of the outputs due to each input acting alone. </label><br>        
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q3di"/><input type="radio" name="q3" value="d" id="q3d"><label for="q3d">All of the above.                                                                                                            </label><br>
    </ul>
    
<script>
